{"title_page": "Veronika Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1", "text_new": "{{short description|Slovakian Paralympic shooter}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n|headercolor    = \n|name           = Veronika Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1\n|image          = Veronika Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1 1.jpg\n|caption        = Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1 in 2016\n|native_name    = \n|native_name_lang = \n|residence      = \n|birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1983|2|9}}\n|birth_place    = [[Trnava]], Slovakia\n|death_date     = \n|death_place    = \n|height         =\n|weight         = \n|coach          = \n|retired        = \n|regionals      = \n|nationals      = \n|pb             = \n|medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport|Women's [[shooting para sport]]}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{SVK}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008 Beijing]]|[[Shooting at the 2008 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 10 metre air rifle standing SH1|10 m air rifle standing SH1]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio]]|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 10 metre air rifle standing SH1|10 m air rifle standing SH1]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio]]|{{nowrap|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Mixed 10m air rifle prone SH1|Mixed 10 m air rifle prone SH1]]}}}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio]]|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 50m rifle 3 positions SH1|50 m rifle 3 positions SH1]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2012 Summer Paralympics|2012 London]]|[[Shooting at the 2012 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 50 metre rifle 3 positions SH1|50 m rifle 3 positions SH1]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Veronika Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1''' (born February 9, 1983) is a [[Slovakia]]n Paralympic shooter who won 3 golds at the [[2014 IPC Shooting World Cup]] in [[Fort Benning]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.paralympic.org/news/vadovicova-seals-triple-world-cup-gold-usa|title=Vadovicova seals triple World Cup gold in USA|publisher=[[International Paralympic Committee|IPC]]|date=10 June 2014|accessdate=12 December 2014|url-status=live|archivedate=13 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213035522/http://www.paralympic.org/news/vadovicova-seals-triple-world-cup-gold-usa|df=dmy-all}}</ref> where she competed against [[Matt Skelhon]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://paralympics.org.uk/news/vadovicova-and-skelhon-to-go-head-to-head-at-last-shooting-world-cup-before|title=Vadovicova and Skelhon to go head-to-head at last shooting World Cup before worlds|publisher=[[British Paralympic Association|BPA]]|date=6 March 2014|accessdate=12 December 2014|url-status=live|archivedate=13 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213035654/http://paralympics.org.uk/news/vadovicova-and-skelhon-to-go-head-to-head-at-last-shooting-world-cup-before|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In [[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008 Paralympic Games]] in [[Beijing]], [[China]], she won gold medal for her participation at the 10 meter SH1. Prior to it, she was a gold medalist at the 2006 [[World Shooting Para Sport Championships|World Shooting Championships]] where she competed in three-position 50-meter rifle event.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/paralympics/2008-09/07/content_7005817.htm|title=Slovakia's Veronika Vadovicova wins 1st Paralympic gold|agency=[[Xinhua News Agency]]|work=[[China Daily]]|date=7 September 2008|accessdate=12 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213040021/http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/paralympics/2008-09/07/content_7005817.htm|url-status=live|archivedate=13 December 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref> On October 24, 2014 she won a gold medal at the [[2014 IPC Shooting European Championships]].<ref>{{cite news|date=October 24, 2013|accessdate=12 December 2014|url=http://www.insidethegames.biz/paralympics/summer-sports/shooting/1016650-vadovicova-fires-way-to-third-gold-and-european-record|author=Gary Anderson|title=Vadovicova fires way to third gold and European record|work=Inside the Games|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140816233137/http://www.insidethegames.biz/paralympics/summer-sports/shooting/1016650-vadovicova-fires-way-to-third-gold-and-european-record|archivedate=16 August 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn March 15, 2016 Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1 broke the R3 (mixed 10m air rifle prone SH1) qualification world record on the opening day of competition at the IPC Shooting World Cup in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.paralympic.org/news/vadovicova-breaks-world-record-shooting-world-cup|title=Vadovicova breaks world record at shooting World Cup|publisher=IPC|date=15 March 2014|accessdate=9 April 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IPC profile|surname=Vadovicova|givenname=Veronika}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vadovicova, Veronika}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Slovak female sport shooters]]\n[[Category:Paralympic shooters of Slovakia]]\n[[Category:Paralympic gold medalists for Slovakia]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for Slovakia]]\n[[Category:Paralympic bronze medalists for Slovakia]]\n[[Category:Paralympic medalists in shooting]]\n[[Category:Shooters at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Shooters at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Shooters at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2008 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Trnava]]\n\n\n{{Slovakia-sportshooting-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Slovakian Paralympic shooter}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n|headercolor    = \n|name           = Veronika Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1\n|image          = Veronika Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1 1.jpg\n|caption        = Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1 in 2016\n|native_name    = \n|native_name_lang = \n|residence      = \n|birth_date     = {{Birth date and age|1983|2|9}}\n|birth_place    = [[Trnava]], Slovakia\n|death_date     = \n|death_place    = \n|height         =\n|weight         = \n|coach          = \n|retired        = \n|regionals      = \n|nationals      = \n|pb             = \n|medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport|Women's [[shooting para sport]]}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{SVK}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Paralympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2008 Summer Paralympics|2008 Beijing]]|[[Shooting at the 2008 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 10 metre air rifle standing SH1|10 m air rifle standing SH1]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio]]|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 10 metre air rifle standing SH1|10 m air rifle standing SH1]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio]]|{{nowrap|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Mixed 10m air rifle prone SH1|Mixed 10 m air rifle prone SH1]]}}}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2016 Summer Paralympics|2016 Rio]]|[[Shooting at the 2016 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 50m rifle 3 positions SH1|50 m rifle 3 positions SH1]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[2012 Summer Paralympics|2012 London]]|[[Shooting at the 2012 Summer Paralympics \u2013 Women's 50 metre rifle 3 positions SH1|50 m rifle 3 positions SH1]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Veronika Vadovi\u010dov\u00e1''' (born February 9, 1983) is a [[Slovakia]]n Paralympic shooter who won 3 golds at the [[2014 IPC Shooting World Cup]] in [[Fort Benning]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.paralympic.org/news/vadovicova-seals-triple-world-cup-gold-usa|title=Vadovicova seals triple World Cup gold in USA|publisher=[[International Paralympic Committee|IPC]]|date=10 June 2014|accessdate=12 December 2014|url-status=live|archivedate=13 December 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141213035522/http://www.paralympic.org/news/vadovicova-seals-triple-world-cup-gold-usa|df=dmy-all}}</ref> where she competed against [[Matt Skelhon]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://paralympics.org.uk/news/vadovicova-and-skelhon-to-go-hea